(458, 20, '2017-12-20 15:35:44', '2017-12-20 14:35:44', 'Religious leaders like my friends Rev. Jim Wallis and Rabbi David Saperstein and Nathan Diament are working for justice and fighting for change. Because it\'s not who we are. We can recognize the truth that\'s at the heart of the UCC: that the conversation is not over; that our roles are not defined; that through ancient texts and modern voices, God is still speaking, challenging us to change not just our own lives, but the world around us. But for all those who scratched and clawed their way to get a piece of the American Dream, there were many who didn\'t make it - those who were ultimately defeated, in one way or another, by discrimination. And you know what - it\'s worked before.\r\n\r\nBut it is a story that has seared into my genetic makeup the idea that this nation is more than the sum of its parts - that out of many, we are truly one. That promise is our greatest inheritance. It was a peaceful and determined insistence upon the ideals at the center of America\'s founding.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-516\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/QAGII-300x215.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"215\" />\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_515\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-515\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/fronton_face-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /> 19/09/2008 - le peristyle, la colonnade et le fronton du Palais Bourbon[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_514\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-514\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/facade-hotel-de-lassay-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /> 22/02/2011: l\'Hotel de Lassay - vue de nacelle[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_511\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"225\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-511\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/bibliotheque-2i-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /> 24/09/2007: Palais Bourbon,<br />photo Leaf HD, fichier .MOS disponible[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_513\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-513\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bureau-depute-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /> Nov 2012 : bureau d\'un député au 101 rue de l\'Université (bureau de M. François-Michel Lambert) - patrimoine[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_510\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-510\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/AN_3373_90-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /> 11/03/2014 : la Colonnade ou Peristyle et le pont de la Concorde (nuit)[/caption]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-512\" src=\"http://172.20.0.5/Eneko-blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/colonnadeBBRface-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" />\r\n\r\nIt\'s a journey that takes us back to our nation\'s founding, when none other than a UCC church inspired the Boston Tea Party and helped bring an Empire to its knees. Understanding this reality requires a reminder of how we arrived at this point. And we will match promising Muslim students with internships in America; invest in on-line learning for teachers and children around the world; and create a new online network, so a teenager in Kansas can communicate instantly with a teenager in Cairo.\r\n\r\nIn the following century, men and women of faith waded into the battles over prison reform and temperance, public education and women\'s rights - and above all, abolition. Well it\'s time for them to own their failure. Yes, we must provide more ladders to success for young men who fall into lives of crime and despair.\r\n\r\nJohn Kerry believes in an America where all Americans can afford the same health coverage our politicians in Washington have for themselves. We worship an awesome God in the Blue States, and we don\'t like federal agents poking around in our libraries in the Red States. In that time, he\'s said no to higher fuel-efficiency standards for cars, no to investments in renewable energy, no to renewable fuels. And it is that promise that forty five years ago today, brought Americans from every corner of this land to stand together on a Mall in Washington, before Lincoln\'s Memorial, and hear a young preacher from Georgia speak of his dream. It was innovation in Muslim communities that developed the order of algebra; our magnetic compass and tools of navigation; our mastery of pens and printing; our understanding of how disease spreads and how it can be healed. That is why I am committed to working with American Muslims to ensure that they can fulfill zakat.\r\n\r\nThank you very much everybody.', 'La délégation aux collectivités territoriales et à la décentralisation tient son président', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-delegation-aux-collectivites-territoriales-et-a-la-decentralisation-tient-son-president', '', '', '2018-02-08 03:23:37', '2018-02-08 02:23:37', '', 0, 'http://blog.eneko.co/?p=458', 0, 'post', '', 0),
